Create an project in firebase
enable google auth
enable realtime database and storage
Select firebase in project settings and follow the steps to get `lib/firebase_options.dart`

For debug login
https://developers.google.com/android/guides/client-auth
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/54557479/flutter-and-google-sign-in-plugin-platformexceptionsign-in-failed-com-google

in short just run
```
keytool -list -v \
-alias androiddebugkey -keystore ~/.android/debug.keystore
```
and copy pasta the sha fingerprint

refs
https://github.com/Twistedben/Great-Places


Real-timeDatabase
"PlantsType" - for all the available plant species
"PlantDetails" - for all data for plants


For the storage
Create 2 folders `static`, `userUploads`
for `static` the file syntax is like - `static/PLANT_SCIENTIFIC_NAME.jpg`
for `userUploads` the syntax is -	   `userUploads/PLANT_SCIENTIFIC_NAME/UID.jpg`
